          "date": "2021-02-22 07:47:40.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-14459 mdt: autosplit directory during create",
        "message": "LU-14459 mdt: autosplit directory during create\n\nAuto-split directories over available MDTs at creation time so\nthat performance and capacity scales as the directory grows,\nrather than waiting until the directory is accessed since not\nall workloads read the directory during file creation, and that\nresults in a much large number of remote directory entries.\n\nSeparate out the logic for directory split so that it can be\nused in the create path.\nTODO:\n- update la_dirent_count when directory entries are added/removed\n- la_dirent_count doesn't need to be totally accurate, directory\n  will still split if it grows large, or eventually on access\n- add a call to mdt_should_auto_split()/mdt_auto_split_add() in\n  dirent_add so that the split happens during file create\n\nTest-Parameters: forbuildonly\nFixes: a336d7c7c1cd (\"LU-11025 dne: directory restripe and auto split\")\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ia66c818ebb5eed4dfb36ec19d2e672fe7734b99a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
